title: Shift Into Turbo: Part 1
description: Divatox returns to Earth seeking vengeance against the Power Rangers Turbo.

title: Shift Into Turbo: Part 2
description: The Turbo Rangers race to stop Divatox from destroying the Angel Grove power plant during their graduation ceremony.

title: Shift Into Turbo: Part 3
description: Zordon and Alpha 5 bid farewell to the planet Earth as Divatox escalates her assault on Angel Grove.

title: Shadow Rangers
description: Divatox's Chromite steals the Turbo Rangers' morphing energy to create evil shadow Rangers.

title: Transmission Impossible
description: Arriving from the Planet Inquiris to deliver a message of great importance to Dimitria, the alien Visceron is brought down by Divatox, and when he refuses to talk, she meddles with his mind and turns him against the Turbo Rangers. Meanwhile, Tanya's KAGV radio show is targeted both by Divatox (a detonator is placed on the transmitter tower) and the Bulk & Skull Chimps (they hope to get noticed as humans by getting on the air!)

title: Rally Ranger
description: Participating in a soapbox-car derby, Justin contends with a brutal pre-teen bully, named Warren, who's prepared to win at any cost. Meanwhile, with his detonator-making prowess unappreciated on Divatox's Subcraft, Porto, feeling dejected, strikes out on his own, giving the Rangers big trouble! The lack of the tech expert doesn't stop Elgar from completing a detonator and sticking it in Warren's racer. Also, the Bulk & Skull Chimps hijack the previous year's winning racer in an effort to become famous and get turned back into humans.

title: Built for Speed
description: Adam battles the lightning-quick Demon Racer as he tries to stop his peers from a dangerous drag race.

title: Bicycle Built for the Blues
description: Justin is trapped on a speeding bicycle in an explosive countdown to zero.

title: The Whole Lie
description: Divatox's Mouth Piece Monster makes Justin lie constantly with a Piranhatron appearing for every lie.

title: Glyph Hanger
description: Divatox summons her ancient Egyptian ex-fiance Pharaoh to battle the Turbo Rangers.

title: Weight and See
description: Divatox sends Numbor to cause Angel Grove to sink into the ocean while Kat worries about her weight.

title: Alarmed and Dangerous
description: Divatox's forces set off false fire alarms all over Angel Grove as Justin deals with school bullies.

title: The Millennium Message
description: The Blue Senturion time travels to present-day Angel Grove with a message from the future for Dimitria.

title: A Drive to Win
description: Divatox sends Electrovolt to Angel Grove to ruin Adam's soccer team.

title: Cars Attacks
description: Wolfgang Amadeus Griller comes to Angel Grove in order to transform automobiles to life.

title: Honey, I Shrunk the Rangers: Part 1
description: The Power Rangers are shrunk to the size of insects.

title: Honey, I Shrunk the Rangers: Part 2
description: The micronized Turbo Rangers go on an action-packed trip trying to escape from Divatox's Subcraft.

title: Passing the Torch: Part 1
description: Visited by her mother Mama D, Divatox is inspired to take down the Turbo Rangers by removing their leader. While heading to the outskirts of Angel Grove to go camping with Adam, Justin, and Tanya, Tommy & Kat are ambushed by Piranahtron. A pair of young teens on a bus in the midst of moving to the area, T.J. (a wannabe professional baseball batter) and Cassie (a wannabe singing star), spot the disturbance and come to the Rangers' aid. But will they be too late to save Tommy? Meanwhile, the other three Ranger Teens must contend with both a Putrapod and the Flamite monster at their campsite.

title: Passing the Torch: Part 2
description: Tommy, Kat, Adam, and Tanya pass their powers on to a new generation of Power Rangers.

title: Stitch Witchery
description: Ashley is excited when she gets a job working with an extravagant fashion designer. She's unaware, though, that the designer, Delisha Enevil, is actually a monster of Divatox's. Ashley's ugly plaid jackets are mass produced by Piranahtron overnight. But the jackets are infused with the monster's magic, making anyone who wears them cruel, greedy, and evil. It's bad enough with all of the Rangers, sans Ashley, put them on, but when Blue Senturion gets tricked into one, he soon goes on another rampage, this time including a jacket-clad Robo Racer! Meanwhile, Bulk & Skull, back to humans but invisible, get mischievous around Angel Grove and the Juice Bar.

title: The Wheel of Fate
description: Two intelligent cars from outer space called Lightning Cruiser and Storm Blaster travel to Earth.

title: Trouble by the Slice
description: Divatox is struck by amnesia while the Power Rangers battle evil pizzas.

title: The Phantom Phenomenon
description: The mysterious Phantom Ranger appears on Earth to assist the Power Rangers.

title: Vanishing Act
description: The Rangers try to uncover why everything around them is disappearing including the Power Chamber.

title: When Time Freezes Over
description: Divatox attempts to control time in order to freeze the planet Earth.

title: The Darkest Day
description: General Havoc reinforces Divatox helping her capture the Turbo Megazord.

title: One Last Hope
description: With no way to defend Angel Grove, the Rangers turn to the Phantom Ranger for assistance.

title: The Fall of the Phantom
description: General Havoc and Divatox set a trap for the Phantom Ranger in order to capture his powerful Phantom Ruby.

title: Clash of the Megazords
description: The Turbo Rangers race to stop the Turbo Megazord and save the Phantom Ranger as his life force ebbs away.

title: The Robot Ranger
description: Justin suspects that his fellow Rangers have been replaced by robots.

title: Beware the Third Wish
description: The Wicked Wisher grants Divatox three wishes. One of which she uses to turn the Blue Senturion evil.

title: Gardner of Evil
description: The Power Rangers hurry to find the third wishing coin and restore the Blue Senturion.

title: Fire in Your Tank
description: The Torch Tiger steals the Turbo Rangers' super fuel turning him into an arsonist nightmare.

title: The Turn of the Wretched Wrench
description: Ashley finds her auto mechanics class more difficult than she anticipated which is further complicated by her fellow student, the Maniac Mechanic.

title: Spirit of the Woods
description: T.J. meets a mysterious young boy in the forest named Erutan.

title: The Song of Confusion
description: Cassie's new rock band turns out to be more than she bargained for.

title: The Accident
description: When Carlos injures a rival, even he isn't sure if it was really by accident.

title: Cassie's Best Friend
description: Cassie's uncannily smart dog Jetson is transformed into a human following a misfire by Divatox's latest monster, Mr. Goorific. Bulk & Skull are hired to help find the missing dog. In human form, Jetson, calling himself Jethro, helps Cassie cope with the loss of her canine best friend and does his best to cheer her up. But with the monster and Elgar's repaired Terrorzord on the horizon, that happiness could be short lived...

title: The Curve Ball
description: T.J. needs to learn how to hit a curve ball if he's going to save his baseball team's chances of victory as well as the world.

title: Carlos and the Count
description: An encounter with a mutated lunar bat leaves Carlos with an aversion to sunlight, and a powerful thirst - for blood!

title: Little Strong Man
description: Justin has trouble trying out for sports, as he's too small and young to compete with the other teens. When an ant, mutated by Bulk & Skull's strange exterminator spray, bites him, he discovers he now has super strength! This makes him a hit with athletics, but the side effect is he's unable to morph. He's forced to choose between a life as a Ranger or a life as a dumb jock. Meanwhile, Divatox prepares to bring to Earth the first of her three Evil Zords, the first being her very own bird-like Divazord.

title: The Rival Rangers
description: Ashley falls for a new guy, Bobby. Cassie, though, has the same feelings, and saw him first. The two gals get rather down and dirty in competing for him. Meanwhile, the aptly named Sharkzord, is piloted by Porto in battle against our heroes.

title: Parts and Parcel
description: Bulk and Skull are blamed for the thefts of several mechanical parts from the "Super Duper Fast Delivery" service they've begun working for. TJ attempts to help prove their innocence, since the parts are actually being stole by Piranahtrons to aid in the repairing of the Evil Zords. Speaking of which, the third and final one, Rygog's Catzord, is unveiled, as all three of the Evil Zords are reunited on Earth to battle against the Rescue Megazord, Turbo Megazord, and Robo Racer, for one last big battle!

title: Chase Into Space: Part 1
description: Justin faces the possibility of having to move away as against overwhelming odds, the Turbo Rangers charge into their final battle.

title: Chase Into Space: Part 2
description: The remaining Power Rangers blast off into outer space to try and save Zordon.
